labels.en: Immersed Tunnel Ontology - Structural Systems Module

comments.en:
Structural systems module providing comprehensive classification and specifications for immersed tunnel structural design.
      Aligned with GBT 51318-2019 "Immersed Tunnel Design Standard" covering structural design, joint systems, and foundation integration.
      
      This module encompasses:
      - Settlement-based joint design classes for IMMTD05
      - Longitudinal structural system design for IMMTD06
      - Tunnel segment geometry and specifications
      - Joint design and waterproofing requirements
      - Foundation integration requirements
      
      STANDARDS ALIGNMENT:
      - Structural design methodology per GBT 51318-2019
      - Joint design requirements and specifications
      - Segment division logic and optimization

Structural load-bearing capacity verified through comprehensive structural calculations per GBT 51318-2019 Section 8.1.1 during prefabrication, towing, mooring, immersion, construction, and operational stages. Analysis based on most unfavorable load combinations per Section 8.1.2 in both transverse and longitudinal directions, with structural safety verified under ultimate and serviceability limit states. Transverse calculations per Section 8.3.1 use plane strain models considering water pressure, soil cover load, lateral earth pressure, and internal load/ballast. Value expressed in kN.
